<li class="thin-divide-bottom comment neutral read"
  data-post-negative="-3"
  data-post-positive="24"
  data-user-vote="neutral"
  data-post-id="40789215"
  data-poster-id="523261"
  id="comment-40789215"
  
  data-user-sentiment="neutral"
  
  data-post-sentiment-totals="{&quot;agree&quot;:&quot;5&quot;,&quot;interesting&quot;:&quot;6&quot;,&quot;funny&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;addsto&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;disagree&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;inaccurate&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;pointless&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;abusive&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}">
  
  <header class="byline">
    <div class="author-rank">
      <span class="author" data-post-author="_myk">
        <a href="/civis/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=523261" rel="nofollow">_myk</a>
        <span class="rank">Wise, Aged Ars Veteran</span>
      </span>
      
    </div>
    <aside class="icons">
      
        <a href="?comments=1&amp;post=40789215&amp;mode=quote#reply" class='quotelink icon' rel='nofollow' title="Reply">reply</a>
      
      <a href="http://arstechnica.com/science/2022/03/exploring-the-counterintuitive-mysteries-of-black-holes-with-paul-sutter/?comments=1&post=40789215#comment-40789215" title="2022-03-30T14:19:44+00:00" rel="nofollow" class="timeago datetime">Wed Mar 30, 2022 9:19 am</a>
      <ul class="comment-tags-list">
      
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </header>
  <div class="body">
    My head canon for black holes is that there's an opposite anti-mass universe where time travels backwards (from our point of view) and black holes are spewing mass &amp; light into that universe until eventually everything collapses into a big crunch (which sets off our big bang, or the next universe).<br /><br />Feel it's got to be something neat and tidy (in terms of balancing out conservation of energy)
    
  </div>
