  data-post-sentiment-totals="{&quot;agree&quot;:&quot;3&quot;,&quot;interesting&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;funny&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;addsto&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;disagree&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;inaccurate&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;pointless&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;abusive&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}">
  
  <header class="byline">
    <div class="author-rank">
      <span class="author" data-post-author="dwrd">
        <a href="/civis/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=683873" rel="nofollow">dwrd</a>
        <span class="rank">Ars Scholae Palatinae</span>
      </span>
      <a class="subscriber" href="/store/product/subscriptions/">et Subscriptor</a>
    </div>
    <aside class="icons">
      
        <a href="?comments=1&amp;post=40789594&amp;mode=quote#reply" class='quotelink icon' rel='nofollow' title="Reply">reply</a>
      
      <a href="http://arstechnica.com/science/2022/03/exploring-the-counterintuitive-mysteries-of-black-holes-with-paul-sutter/?comments=1&post=40789594#comment-40789594" title="2022-03-30T16:09:59+00:00" rel="nofollow" class="timeago datetime">Wed Mar 30, 2022 11:09 am</a>
      <ul class="comment-tags-list">
      
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </header>
  <div class="body">
    <div class="quotetitle"><a href="https://arstechnica.com/civis/viewtopic.php?p=40789554#p40789554" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">BatCrapCrazy</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So lady physicist ( forgot her name) says that black holes have accretion discs, so that means that a black must have a well defined equator and with that a north and south. somehow sounds strange to me.</div><br /><br />Those features are defined relative to the rotation of the object. Since angular momentum is conserved, we believe most black holes rotate, and therefore there will be an axis of rotation, and you can define the equator relative to that. From there, North and South are defined by convention (the &quot;right hand rule&quot;).
    
  </div>
  <footer>
    <div class="tools-info">
